id": 2,\n      "description": "Read a book",\n      "done": true\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n#### Project Structure\n```plaintext\ncli_todo_app/\n├── main.py               # Entry point for the application\n├── task_manager.py       # Contains Task Management Module\n├── json_handler.py       # Contains JSON Handling Module\n└── cli_interface.py      # Contains CLI Interface Module\n```\n\n#### Data Flow\n1. The application starts up and calls the `load_tasks` function to populate the task list from a JSON file.\n2. The user interacts with the CLI to execute commands (add, view, complete, delete tasks).\n3. Each command triggers the respective function in the Task Management Module.\n4. Changes to tasks are saved back to the JSON file via the `save_tasks` function on application exit.\n\n### Next Steps\n- Write the design document in the knowledge base for future reference and implementation guidance.\n- Return control back to the Project Manager once documentation is complete.\n\nI will now draft and write the design document in the knowledge base.', type='ThoughtEvent')}
