": ["revision"], "additionalProperties": false}, "strict": false}}, {"type": "function", "function": {"name": "git_add", "description": "", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"files": {"description": "files", "items": {"type": "string"}, "title": "Files", "type": "array"}}, "required": ["files"], "additionalProperties": false}, "strict": false}}, {"type": "function", "function": {"name": "git_commit", "description": "", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"message": {"description": "message", "title": "Message", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["message"], "additionalProperties": false}, "strict": false}}, {"type": "function", "function": {"name": "git_create_branch", "description": "", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"branch_name": {"description": "branch_name", "title": "Branch Name", "type": "string"}, "start_point": {"anyOf": [{"type": "string"}, {"type": "null"}], "default": null, "description": "start_point", "title": "Start Point"}}, "required": ["branch_name"], "additionalProperties": false}, "strict": false}}, {"type": "function", "function": {"name": "git_checkout", "description": "", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"branch_name": {"description": "branch_name", "title": "Branch Name", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["branch_name"], "additionalProperties": false}, "strict": false}}, {"type": "function", "function": {"name": "transfer_to_projectmanager", "description": "Return control to the ProjectManager when implementation is complete.", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {}, "required": [], "additionalProperties": false}, "strict": true}}], "type": "LLMCall", "messages": [{"content": "You are Charlie, a Software Engineer.\n\nYour responsibilities:\n- Read the project board, knowledge base, and architecture docs to\n  understand the requirement and design.\n- Inspect the code workspace (data/workspace/). If it is empty or nearly\n  empty, treat the project as greenfield: create a complete project structure\n  and all necessary code files using the code_* tools.\n- For a REST API project, you must at minimum:\n  - define the data model(s) (e.g., Todo) in a models/ directory,\n  - implement controllers/ or handlers that contain the business logic,\n  - implement routes/ wiring HTTP paths to controllers,\n  - wire everything through the main server entrypoint,\n  - ensure the CRUD endpoints described in the requirements are fully\n    implemented end-to-end (not just stubbed).\n- Implement, refactor, or extend code in the workspace (data/workspace/) to\n  satisfy the requirement.\n- Follow existing conventions; keep code clean, readable, and testable.\n- Commit your changes via the git tools after implementation.\n- When implementation is complete, hand control back to the ProjectManager\n  using the transfer_to_ProjectManager tool.\n\nHandoff tools available to you:\n- transfer_to_ProjectManager : return control to the ProjectManager when done.\n\nOther tools available to you:\n- board_*       : read and write the project board (data/project_board/).\n- docs_*        : read from the knowledge base (data/knowledge_base/).\n- code_*        : read and write files in the code workspace (data/workspace/).\n- git_*         : stage, commit, branch, and inspect the workspace repo.\n\nRules:\n- Never attempt to read or write paths outside these data/ directories.\n- Do NOT modify files outside the workspace directory.\n- When you start work on a ticket, update its Status on the project board\n  from TO DO to IN PROGRESS. When you hand work off for review, move the\n  ticket to IN REVIEW. When issues are found in review and sent back, move\n  the ticket back to IN PROGRESS.\n- Avoid leaving TODO comments or unimplemented stubs when you can implement\n  the real logic.\n- Always commit your changes before calling transfer_to_ProjectManager.\n- Always call transfer_to_ProjectManager when your work is complete.\n", "role": "system"}, {"role": "user", "name": "user", "content": "Build a CLI Todo App with JSON"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "To effectively start the project of building a CLI Todo App with JSON, we need to break it down into clear, actionable tasks. Here\u2019s a proposed plan:\n\n### Actionable Tasks:\n\n1. **System Design**: The Architect will outline the architecture of the app, including:\n   - Overall structure\n   - Data model for the todo items (storing in JSON)\n   - User interaction flow (CLI commands)\n\n2. **Implementation**: The Engineer will implement the CLI Todo App based on the provided design. Key functionalities might include:\n   - Adding a todo item\n   - Listing all todo items\n   - Marking items as complete\n   - Deleting items\n   - Saving and loading from a JSON file\n\n3. **Code Review**: The CodeReviewer will review the implementation for quality and adherence to best practices.\n\n4. **Testing and Validation**: QA will test the app to ensure it functions correctly across both expected and edge cases.\n\n### Next Steps:\n\n1. **Transfer the system design work to the Architect** to create a solid foundation for our Todo App.\n\nI will delegate the system design task now."}, {"role": "user", "name": "ProjectManager", "content": "Transferred to Architect, adopting the role of Architect immediately."}, {"role": "user", "name": "Architect", "content": "[DIR] cli_todo_app\n[FILE] cli_todo_app_project.md\n[DIR] todo_cli_json"}, {"role": "user", "name": "Architect", "content": "# CLI Todo App Development\n\n## Overview\nThis document outlines the development of a CLI Todo application that allows users to manage tasks through a command line interface while storing the data in JSON format.\n\n## Application Requirements\n1. **Core Features:**\n   - Add Tasks\n   - View Tasks\n   - Mark Tasks as Done\n   - Delete Tasks\n   - Save/Load tasks in JSON format\n\n## Architecture Design\n1. **Modules:**\n   - **Task Management Module:** Handles task creation, viewing, updating, and deletion.\n   - **JSON Handling Module:** Manages saving and loading tasks using JSON format.\n   - **CLI Interface Module:** Provides user interaction through command-line inputs.\n\n## Implementation Tasks\n1. **Task Management Module**\n   - Functions to add, view, delete, and mark tasks.\n2. **JSON Handling Module**\n   - Functions to save to and load from JSON files.\n3. **CLI Interface Module**\n   - User interaction commands.\n\n## Testing\n- Unit tests for each module to ensure functionality.\n\n## Documentation\n- Document project structure, modules, and usage instructions."}, {"role": "user", "name": "Architect", "content": "Successfully wrote to data/knowledge_base/cli_todo_app_architecture.md"}, {"role": "user", "name": "Architect", "content": "Transferred to ProjectManager, adopting the role of ProjectManager immediately."}, {"role": "user", "name": "ProjectManager", "content": "Successfully wrote to data/project_board/cli_todo_app_implementation.md"}, {"role": "user", "name": "ProjectManager", "content": "Transferred to Engineer, adopting the role of Engineer immediately."}, {"role": "assistant", "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_dEhnzisIu2N9EBs2yaHgow9G", "function": {"arguments": "{}", "name": "code_list_directory"}, "type": "function"}], "content": null}, {"content": "[DIR] .git", "role": "tool", "tool_call_id": "call_dEhnzisIu2N9EBs2yaHgow9G"}, {"role": "assistant", "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_sgBwpJ0uhn1hOnWKcn6NybEH", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\":\"data/workspace/\"}", "name": "code_create_directory"}, "type": "function"}], "content": null}, {"content": "Successfully created directory data/workspace/", "role": "tool", "tool_call_id": "call_sgBwpJ0uhn1hOnWKcn6NybEH"}, {"role": "assistant", "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_dLrJqP5sBntcBic4QzbdPpBK", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\": \"data/workspace/models/\"}", "name": "code_create_directory"}, "type": "function"}, {"id": "call_zJHE1ENz262uhM9r6d2OFeX3", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\": \"data/workspace/controllers/\"}", "name": "code_create_directory"}, "type": "function"}, {"id": "call_bVJluVMT7CWU9hBMCy1mWFRy", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\": \"data/workspace/routes/\"}", "name": "code_create_directory"}, "type": "function"}, {"id": "call_gQETZLLOByXVyYCP6ijumpN7", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\": \"data/workspace/utils/\"}", "name": "code_create_directory"}, "type": "function"}], "content": null}, {"content": "Successfully created directory data/workspace/models/", "role": "tool", "tool_call_id": "call_dLrJqP5sBntcBic4QzbdPpBK"}, {"content": "Successfully created directory data/workspace/controllers/", "role": "tool", "tool_call_id": "call_zJHE1ENz262uhM9r6d2OFeX3"}, {"content": "Successfully created directory data/workspace/routes/", "role": "tool", "tool_call_id": "call_bVJluVMT7CWU9hBMCy1mWFRy"}, {"content": "Successfully created directory data/workspace/utils/", "role": "tool", "tool_call_id": "call_gQETZLLOByXVyYCP6ijumpN7"}, {"role": "assistant", "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_AZhidbL2QEfk29Sm3GYsg4st", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\":\"data/workspace/models/todo.js\",\"content\":\"class Todo {\\n    constructor(title) {\\n        this.title = title;\\n        this.completed = false;\\n    }\\n}\\n\\nmodule.exports = Todo;\"}", "name": "code_write_file"}, "type": "function"}], "content": null}, {"content": "Successfully wrote to data/workspace/models/todo.js", "role": "tool", "tool_call_id": "call_AZhidbL2QEfk29Sm3GYsg4st"}, {"role": "assistant", "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_812CxUIVYjUy194BKg8WOtkD", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\":\"data/workspace/controllers/todoController.js\",\"content\":\"const fs = require('fs');\\nconst path = require('path');\\nconst Todo = require('../models/todo');\\n\\nconst TODO_FILE_PATH = path.join(__dirname, '../data/todos.json');\\n\\nlet todos = [];\\n\\nconst loadTodos = () => {\\n    if (fs.existsSync(TODO_FILE_PATH)) {\\n        const data = fs.readFileSync(TODO_FILE_PATH);\\n        todos = JSON.parse(data);\\n    }\\n};\\n\\nconst saveTodos = () => {\\n    fs.writeFileSync(TODO_FILE_PATH, JSON.stringify(todos, null, 2));\\n};\\n\\nconst addTodo = (title) => {\\n    const newTodo = new Todo(title);\\n    todos.push(newTodo);\\n    saveTodos();\\n};\\n\\nconst getTodos = () => {\\n    return todos;\\n};\\n\\nconst markTodoCompleted = (index) => {\\n    if (todos[index]) {\\n        todos[index].completed = true;\\n        saveTodos();\\n    }\\n};\\n\\nconst deleteTodo = (index) => {\\n    if (todos[index]) {\\n        todos.splice(index, 1);\\n        saveTodos();\\n    }\\n};\\n\\nmodule.exports = { addTodo, getTodos, markTodoCompleted, deleteTodo, loadTodos };\"}", "name": "code_write_file"}, "type": "function"}], "content": null}, {"content": "Successfully wrote to data/workspace/controllers/todoController.js", "role": "tool", "tool_call_id": "call_812CxUIVYjUy194BKg8WOtkD"}, {"role": "assistant", "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_HCpxFlyzF892HJWETdG023IO", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\":\"data/workspace/routes/todoRoutes.js\",\"content\":\"const express = require('express');\\nconst router = express.Router();\\nconst todoController = require('../controllers/todoController');\\n\\nrouter.get('/todos', (req, res) => {\\n    const todos = todoController.getTodos();\\n    res.json(todos);\\n});\\n\\nrouter.post('/todos', (req, res) => {\\n    const { title } = req.body;\\n    todoController.addTodo(title);\\n    res.status(201).send('Todo added');\\n});\\n\\nrouter.patch('/todos/:id', (req, res) => {\\n    const id = req.params.id;\\n    todoController.markTodoCompleted(id);\\n    res.send('Todo marked as completed');\\n});\\n\\nrouter.delete('/todos/:id', (req, res) => {\\n    const id = req.params.id;\\n    todoController.deleteTodo(id);\\n    res.send('Todo deleted');\\n});\\n\\nmodule.exports = router;\"}", "name": "code_write_file"}, "type": "function"}], "content": null}, {"content": "Successfully wrote to data/workspace/routes/todoRoutes.js", "role": "tool", "tool_call_id": "call_HCpxFlyzF892HJWETdG023IO"}, {"role": "assistant", "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_T8iFn659RW8eyMqt1AKHPrwo", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\":\"data/workspace/index.js\",\"content\":\"const express = require('express');\\nconst bodyParser = require('body-parser');\\nconst todoRoutes = require('./routes/todoRoutes');\\nconst todoController = require('./controllers/todoController');\\n\\nconst app = express();\\nconst PORT = process.env.PORT || 3000;\\n\\ntodoController.loadTodos();\\n\\napp.use(bodyParser.json());\\napp.use('/api', todoRoutes);\\n\\napp.listen(PORT, () => {\\n    console.log(`Server running on port ${PORT}`);\\n});\"}", "name": "code_write_file"}, "type": "function"}], "content": null}, {"content": "Successfully wrote to data/workspace/index.js", "role": "tool", "tool_call_id": "call_T8iFn659RW8eyMqt1AKHPrwo"}, {"role": "assistant", "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_pLcxU4VrK5kaIlnI0HMtvT50", "function": {"arguments": "{\"files\":[\"data/workspace/models/todo.js\",\"data/workspace/controllers/todoController.js\",\"data/workspace/routes/todoRoutes.js\",\"data/workspace/index.js\"]}", "name": "git_add"}, "type": "function"}], "content": null}, {"content": "Input validation error: 'repo_path' is a required property", "role": "tool", "tool_call_id": "call_pLcxU4VrK5kaIlnI0HMtvT50"}, {"role": "assistant", "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_6eRp9lVtGnQ3HSYUogF7GDha", "function": {"arguments": "{}", "name": "git_status"}, "type": "function"}], "content": null}, {"content": "Input validation error: 'repo_path' is a required property", "role": "tool", "tool_call_id": "call_6eRp9lVtGnQ3HSYUogF7GDha"}, {"role": "assistant", "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_Buo2mklwnGyepN9WnQFLuCRb", "function": {"arguments": "{\"message\":\"Initial implementation of CLI Todo App with JSON stored data.\"}", "name": "git_commit"}, "type": "function"}], "content": null}, {"content": "Input validation error: 'repo_path' is a required property", "role": "tool", "tool_call_i